---

## User Stories & Use Cases

1. **Student:** Snap a photo of waste to know if it is recyclable.  
2. **Parent:** Browse or search for common household items and learn correct disposal methods.  
3. **Young Professional:** Track scan history to monitor recycling habits.  

---

## Key Features & Requirements

**Must-Have (P0):**  
- Image recognition (Plastic, Paper, Glass, Metal, Non-recyclable)  
- Disposal guidance  
- Scan history (offline storage)  

**Should-Have (P1):**  
- Education cards  
- Local recycling center information  

**Nice-to-Have (P2):**  
- Gamification  
- Multi-language support  
- Cloud backup for scan history  

**Out of Scope:**  
- Municipal analytics dashboards  
- Complex cloud features or gamification for MVP  

---

## Design Considerations

- Simple 3-step interaction flow: Open app → Capture/Upload → View result  
- Fast feedback: <5 seconds per classification  
- Clear instructions and visual cues for each category  
- Offline functionality  
- Optimized for mid-range smartphones  

---

## Technical Requirements

- **Platform:** Lovable.ai (no-code)  
- **AI Model:** Google Teachable Machine → TensorFlow Lite (TFLite)  
- **Device Storage:** Local scan history  
- **APIs & Integrations:** Camera, image upload, optional static map for recycling centers  

---

## Constraints & Assumptions

- MVP built on a no-code platform, limiting backend customization  
- Budget constraints: free/no-code tools only  
- Prototype completion in 6–7 days  
- Users have smartphones with camera & storage  
- Core features work offline  

